<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Diamante</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hiya,<P>I'm basically just curious as to what the cheapest possible price is for peridots? <P>I have been buying them from the gnome in rathe mtns since I have been killing HG's and I know he is definitely not the best price.  But he lets me get rid of all my gold and silver.<P>btw he charges me 11pp 3gp<P>I'm curious as to how much cha will get me the best price at vendors. <P>Thanks in advance, Diamante<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Meddik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">10.5 is lowest.<P>I get it with 100 cha and Amiable in Kaladim's rogue guild.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have recently begun raising my faction in FV and am now indifferent. With my whopping 72cha (I keep a stien of Moggok in a bag for buying/selling) I now get them for 11pp, 3gp, 6sp, 7cp. Back when I was dubious, I couldn't get them for less that 16pp and it was easier, cheaper and faster for me to get a port to WC to pop over to that last inn in EC to buy.<P>10.5pp is the cheapest I have ever heard anyone get them, even "warmly", 150+cha chanters don't get better than 10.5.<P>Back when I hunted in Lower Guk or HG's in Rathe Mountains, I actually bound myself at the inn and used that Gnome for my buying and sell. If you are gonna be in that area, he's the best place to shop.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sphynkl</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The last hut in E.C when heading to W.C. I get Peridots (he sells pearls too) for 10p.  <P>HighElf<P>Sphynkl 57 Tunare boy</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sertain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">With 104 charisma after my small amount of charisma gear, i pay 10 plat and 5 gold per stone too.  I am a human and buy in highkeep btw.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Asklepios Deiwos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I buy them in Highkeep.  They love me there.  It's also easier for me to switch into my char suit since the bank is only one room away.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gniss Fleshmender</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I carry my beauty suit with me as I go. I can get to 95, and as long as I con indif or better, I can get them almost anywhere for 10pp5gp.<P>------------------<BR>The patchwork cleric<BR>Domus Divinae<BR>Prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Laresa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have a silk evening tunic that shows some cleavage <G> when buying gems.  (Helps with the male vendors =P)  I also have +7 charisma rings, a stein and charisma bracers I wear when buying gems that brings my charisma to 128, in turn I am able to buy the gems for 10p 5g.  <BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Salina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Another thing to try if you have the time and a friend to help you transfer...<P>Make an enchanter twink, max out that cha and put them in Erudin (Erudite enchanters have the highest starting charisma, or they did).  Have your mule buy them for you.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Not as convenient, but making friends with enchanters and shamans really helps as they have excellent charisma buffs.<P>------------------<BR>Salina Grey<BR>Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous<BR>Guild Leader, Glory's Path</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bodasal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">With my 51st Illusionist with 166 charisma and best faction spell I can't get lower than 10 plat 5 gold.<P>Although I have noticed a trend while playing my cleric of being handed Peridots looted from corpses by other people  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><BR>Pooki , 44th Human Cleric - Erollisi Marr<BR>Bodasal Innuendas , 51st High Elven Channeler - EM<BR>Boddarc , 51st Dark Elf Illusionist - EM</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">10.5 plat in the mines in Kaladim.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Havusin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Paying 5-10 plat for an ench or shammie cha buff will save you money if you buy in stacks.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Reviver</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Best price for peridots is 10.5pp.<P>With my unbuffed charisma at 100ish and high warmly faction with Thurgadim, Freeport, Qeynos and Skyshrine merchants, I will get the best price.<P>You can con warmly, have charisma at 105 and not be able to get the peridots at 10.5pp. That means you haven't reached a high enough warmly faction. Faction grades are just a description for a range of faction points.<P>------------------<BR><B>Reviver Enithsa</B><BR><B>Divine Grace</B><BR><I>Human Cleric of Erollisi Marr</I><BR><I>Erollisi Marr Server</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Huffadopolis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have been able to get best price (10.5pp) from the vendor outside the mage guild in West Freeport while indifferent (via sneaking) and at 115 charisma.  <P>------------------<BR>Huffadopolis Polychronopolis<BR>Level 52 Halfling Vicar<BR>Arma Aquetatis<BR>Lanys T`Vyl</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
